    {
      "id": "10",
      "name": "Description",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "story",
          "data": {
            "list": [
              {
                "artifactPos": "",
                "desc": "<p>\"Why is your sword lying on the ground?\"<br>\"I'm sun-tanning the sword to make it darker.\"<br>\"Why?\"<br>\"Good question, kid. What's the darkest thing you can think of?\"<br>\"Crows?\"<br>\"...Sure. What else?\"<br>\"Hm... Cooking pots!\"<br>\"Good. Keep going. What's underneath the cooking pot?\"<br>\"Fire!\"<br>\"And where does the fire come from?\"<br>The girl thought for a bit.<br>\"Coal! Coal is the darkest thing of all!\"<br>\"That's right! Coal, or carbon, is what makes iron stronger. But I figure I can just darken the sword by tanning it instead.\"<br>With that, he flipped the sword to the other side.</p>",
                "id": "story65306",
                "img": "",
                "title": ""
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
